# Coding Rules

See full spec: `docs/coding-rules.md`

## TypeScript â€” Strict

```typescript
// âťŚ BAD
function process(data: any) { return data.value; }

// âś… GOOD
function process(data: ClientData): number { return data.value; }
```

- No `any` â€” use `unknown` + type guards in catch blocks
- Explicit return types on all functions
- `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections

## Components

```typescript
// âś… Functional component with typed props
interface CardProps { title: string; onPress: () => void; }
const Card: React.FC<CardProps> = ({ title, onPress }): JSX.Element => { ... };
```

- One component per file, under 150 lines
- Conditional renders: ternary + `null` â€” NOT `&&`
- Destructure props at the signature

## Hooks

```typescript
// Business logic in hooks, not screens
export const useClients = () => {
  const [clients, setClients] = useState<Client[]>([]);
  // ... fetch logic
  return { clients, isLoading, error, refetch };
};
```

- Always specify `useEffect` dependency arrays
- Clean up subscriptions in `useEffect` return
- Use `useCallback` for callbacks passed to children
- Use `useMemo` for expensive derived values

## State

```typescript
// âś… Immutable updates
setUser(prev => ({ ...prev, name: 'Jane' }));

// âťŚ Never mutate directly
state.user.name = 'Jane';
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
// âś… Typed errors, never empty catch
try {
  const data = await clientService.getAll();
} catch (error: unknown) {
  if (isApiError(error)) { logger.error(error.code); }
  throw error;
}
```

## Performance

```typescript
// Memoize FlatList renderItem
const renderItem = useCallback(
  ({ item }: { item: Client }) => <ClientCard client={item} />,
  [],
);

// Memoize pure child components
const ClientItem = React.memo(({ client }: Props) => <View />);
```

## Naming

- Booleans: `is`, `has`, `can`, `should` prefix â†’ `isLoading`, `hasError`
- Event handlers: `handle` or `on` prefix â†’ `handlePress`, `onSubmit`
- Constants: `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE`
- No magic numbers â€” extract to named constants

## Imports Order

1. React / React Native core
2. Third-party libraries
3. Absolute internal imports (`@features/`, `@constants/`)
4. Relative imports (same folder)

## Anti-Patterns

- âťŚ `any` type
- âťŚ Class components
- âťŚ Direct state mutation
- âťŚ `&&` conditional render with non-boolean left
- âťŚ `useEffect` without dependency array
- âťŚ Empty `catch` blocks
- âťŚ Magic numbers / hardcoded colors in components
- âťŚ Business logic in screens
